## Overview
Build the `/upcoming` route as a stats-forward, mobile-first UI page. No narrative text — every pixel should communicate data. Inspired by Tapology's row layout and Oddschecker's inline probability display.

---

## File Structure
```
frontend/
  pages/
    upcoming/
      index.tsx          # /upcoming route — event list
  components/
    upcoming/
      EventAccordion.tsx       # Collapsible event row
      FightCard.tsx            # Full fight card inside expanded event
      FightRow.tsx             # Single fight row (collapsed)
      FightRowExpanded.tsx     # Expanded fight row with full breakdown
      WinProbabilityBar.tsx    # Dominant visual bar component
      MethodChip.tsx           # e.g. "60% Decision" chip
      StatDifferential.tsx     # Single key stat differential row
      MethodBreakdown.tsx      # Full KO/Sub/Dec breakdown (expanded)
  lib/
    api/upcoming.ts            # API client functions
  types/
    upcoming.ts                # TypeScript interfaces
```

---

## TypeScript Types (`types/upcoming.ts`)
```typescript
export interface UpcomingEventSummary {
  id: string;
  event_name: string;
  date_proper: string;
  location: string;
  fight_count: number;
  predicted_fight_count: number;
  is_numbered: boolean;
}

export interface KeyDifferential {
  feature_name: string;
  value: number;
  abs_magnitude: number;
}

export interface UpcomingPrediction {
  win_prob_a: number;
  win_prob_b: number;
  method_ko_tko: number;
  method_sub: number;
  method_dec: number;
  model_version: string;
  predicted_at: string;
}

export interface UpcomingFightCard {
  id: string;
  fighter_a_name: string;
  fighter_b_name: string;
  weight_class: string;
  is_main_event: boolean;
  is_title_fight: boolean;
  bout_order: number;
  prediction: UpcomingPrediction | null;
  key_differentials: KeyDifferential[];
}

export interface UpcomingEventDetail {
  id: string;
  event_name: string;
  date_proper: string;
  location: string;
  is_numbered: boolean;
  fights: UpcomingFightCard[];
}
```

---

## API Client (`lib/api/upcoming.ts`)
```typescript
const BASE = '/api/v1/upcoming';

export async function fetchUpcomingEvents(): Promise<UpcomingEventSummary[]> {
  const res = await fetch(`${BASE}/events`);
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Failed to fetch upcoming events');
  return res.json();
}

export async function fetchUpcomingEventDetail(id: string): Promise<UpcomingEventDetail> {
  const res = await fetch(`${BASE}/events/${id}`);
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Failed to fetch event ${id}`);
  return res.json();
}
```

---

## Page: `/upcoming/index.tsx`
- Use `getServerSideProps` (or SWR/React Query) to call `fetchUpcomingEvents()`.
- Render a page header: "Upcoming Events" with subtitle showing count.
- Map events into `<EventAccordion>` components, sorted by date ASC (already sorted by API).
- Show a skeleton loader while fetching.
- Show an empty state if no events returned.

---

## Component: `EventAccordion.tsx`
- Collapsed state shows: event name (bold), date (formatted e.g. "Sat, Jan 18"), location, fight count badge, prediction coverage badge (e.g. "12/14 predicted").
- Numbered events get a gold/accent left border or badge.
- On click: expand and lazy-fetch `fetchUpcomingEventDetail(id)` if not already loaded (cache in local state or React Query).
- Chevron icon rotates 180° on expand (CSS transition).
- Smooth height animation using CSS `max-height` transition or Framer Motion `AnimatePresence`.
- Only one event can be expanded at a time (accordion behaviour) OR allow multiple — choose multiple for better UX on mobile.

---

## Component: `FightCard.tsx`
- Receives `UpcomingEventDetail.fights` array.
- Renders main event first (is_main_event=true), then remaining fights by bout_order DESC.
- Shows a "MAIN EVENT" label above the first fight row.
- Title fights get a belt icon or "TITLE FIGHT" chip.
- Divider lines between fight rows.

---

## Component: `FightRow.tsx` (collapsed)
This is the core scannable unit. At 375px it must show:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Fighter A Name          Fighter B Name           │
│ [████████████░░░░░░░░] 68%  vs  32%             │  ← WinProbabilityBar
│ 🏆 60% Decision   ·  Reach +3"  ·  SLpM +1.2   │  ← MethodChip + 2 key stats
│ Lightweight                              [›]     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- Fighter names: bold, truncated with ellipsis if too long.
- `WinProbabilityBar`: full-width bar, left side = fighter A colour (blue), right side = fighter B colour (red). Percentages shown at each end.
- `MethodChip`: top method by probability, e.g. "60% Decision", "45% KO/TKO". Pill-shaped chip with subtle background.
- Key stat differentials: show top 2 from `key_differentials` array inline (e.g. "Reach +3in", "SLpM +1.4"). Positive = favours A, negative = favours B. Use colour coding (green/red).
- Weight class shown in muted text bottom-left.
- If `prediction === null`: show "Prediction unavailable" in muted italic, no bar.
- Tap anywhere on row to expand.

---

## Component: `FightRowExpanded.tsx`
Expands below the collapsed row (inline, not modal):

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  METHOD BREAKDOWN                               │
│  Decision  ████████████░░░░  60%               │
│  KO/TKO    ██████░░░░░░░░░░  30%               │
│  Sub       ██░░░░░░░░░░░░░░  10%               │
│                                                 │
│  KEY DIFFERENTIALS                              │
│  Reach          Fighter A +3.0 in              │
│  Sig. Str/min   Fighter A +1.4                 │
│  TD Acc %       Fighter B +12%                 │
│  Sub Avg        Fighter B +0.8                 │
│  Str Def %      Fighter A +8%                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- `MethodBreakdown`: three horizontal mini-bars for KO/TKO, Sub, Decision with percentages.
- `StatDifferential` list: all 5 key_differentials from API, each row shows feature name, which fighter it favours, and magnitude. Colour-coded: blue = favours A, red = favours B.
- Feature names should be human-readable (map from snake_case: `avg_sig_str_landed` → "Sig. Str/min").
- No narrative text — pure data rows.

